We recreated the visual hierarchy using Plotly and Dash components.
- Now uses pure `dcc.Graph` elements integrated with Plotly's `plotly_dark` themes to match our exact background colors.
- Custom "metric cards" using Bootstrap layouts and tailored CSS classes.

### ðŸ“ Logs Page ([pages/logs.py](file:///Users/pranavparthasarathy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/fitness-tracker/pages/logs.py))
Centralized all data-entry forms into a robust grid using native Dash inputs and callbacks.
- **Unified Callbacks**: `Input()`, `Output()`, and `State()` handle writes to our [database.py](file:///Users/pranavparthasarathy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/fitness-tracker/database.py) seamlessly without full page reloads.
